Executive Profile
Bridgette P. Heller  General Manager of Medical Nutrition, DanoneAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Ms. Bridgette P. Heller has been General Manager of Medical Nutrition at Danone since July 1, 2017. Ms. Heller served as an Executive Vice President of Early Life Nutrition at Danone since July 1, 2016. Backed by very solid international experience, Ms. Heller has developed expertise in both FMCG and Healthcare. She served as the President of Consumer Care and Executive Vice President of Merck & Co., Inc. (formerly, Schering-Plough Corporation) from March 1, 2010 to ... 2015. Ms. Heller is an Independent Marketing Strategy Consultant. Prior to March 1, 2010, she served as President of Johnson & Johnson's Baby Global Business Unit from 2007 to 2010 and Global President for Baby, Kids and Wound Care from 2005 to 2007. Prior to joining Johnson & Johnson, she was the Managing Partner at Heller Associates from 2004 to 2005, which she founded in 2004. She served as the Chief Executive Officer of Chung's Foods Inc from 2003 to 2004. Ms. Heller spent seventeen years with Kraft Foods, from September 1985 to September 2002, including Executive Vice President and General Manager for the North American Coffee portfolio. She has been an Independent Director at Tech Data Corporation since November 30, 2016. She served as an Independent Director of The ADT Corporation from September 14, 2012 to May 2, 2016. She served as a Director of PCA International Inc. (now Portrait Corporation of America Inc.) from March 1998 to October 2005. Ms. Heller received an MBA from the J. L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management at Northwestern University and received her B.A. in Economics and Computer Studies from Northwestern University.Read Full Background




