	     Bridgette P.  Heller
	     
	  



pharmaceutical company executive



		Bridgette P. Heller, American pharmaceutical company executive. Named a Woman to Watch, Advertising Age, 2008; named one of The 50 Most Powerful Black Women in Business, Black Enterprise magazine, 2006. Board member Girls Inc., Family Service, Westchester, New York; chair Kraft's Operation Opportunity Progressive; chair grant making committee Philip Morris Employee Fund; Member of Executive Leadership Council  (chair).
		
       		



Background




Heller, Bridgette P. was born in 1961 in St. Petersburg, Florida, United States.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor in Computer Studies & Economics, Northwestern University, Illinois, 1983. Master of Business Administration in Marketing, Northwestern University Kellogg Graduate School Management, 1985.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			Assistant product manager Kraft Foods Inc., 1985—1987, product manager, 1987—1991, category manager, 1991—1996, vice president, general manager Gevalia Kaffee, 1996—2000, executive vice president, general manager coffee division, 2000—2003. Chief Executive Officer Chung's Foods, Inc., Houston, 2003—2005. Global president baby, kids and wound care division Johnson & Johnson, New Brunswick, New Jersey, 2005—2010.Executive vice president, president Consumer Health Care Merck & Company, Inc., Whitehouse Station, since 2010. Consultant Avon Cosmetics, since 2004.
			
       			












Membership


			Board member Girls Inc., Family Service, Westchester, New York. Chair Kraft's Operation Opportunity Progressive. Chair grant making committee Philip Morris Employee Fund.Member of Executive Leadership Council  (chair).
			
    			











